You run:
terraform apply
Error:
Error: Provider not installed
❓ Questions:

Root cause?

Which command fixes it?

Why does this happen internally?

Solution :- 
1. Root Cause
Terraform cannot find the required provider plugin in the .terraform directory.

This usually happens when:

You didn’t run terraform init

.terraform/ folder is deleted

New provider added but not initialized

2. Fix Command

terraform init

3. Why This Happens Internally ?
Terraform reads required_providers

Checks .terraform/plugins

If missing → throws error

* terraform init:

Downloads provider binaries

Stores them locally

Creates .terraform.lock.hcl (dependency lock)
